product_name: L'OrealInfallible Up to 32 Hour Fresh Wear Foundation
summary: SummaryL'Oréal Infallible Fresh Wear 32HR Foundation is their most lightweight, breathable, longwear foundation. Defies transfer hour after hour.
details: DetailsFeaturesUp to 32 hour natural finish with buildable coverage, lightweightResists transfer, sweat and remains breathable all dayColor stays true all dayBenefitsAdvanced formula's three oil absorbers resist sweat, water, and transferInfused with SPF 25, non-comedogenic and suitable for all skin typesItem 2538199How To UseApply all over the face with your fingers or a brush, or use a beauty sponge to blend.IngredientsActive: Octinoxate 6.743250%, Titanium Dioxide 3.5910%. Inactive: Water, Dimethicone, Isododecane, Alcohol Denat., Butylene Glycol, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, PEG-10 Dimethicone, Perlite, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Nylon-12, Isopropyl Lauroyl Sarcosinate, Diisopropyl Sebacate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Hdi/Trimethylol Hexyllactone Crosspolymer, Bis-PEG/PPG-14/14 Dimethicone, Magnesium Sulfate, Aluminum Hydroxide, Phenoxyethanol, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Hydrogen Dimethicone, Dipentaerythrityl Tetrahydroxystearate/Tetraisostearate, Fragrance, Silica Silylate, Acrylonitrile/Methyl Methacrylate/Vinylidene Chloride Copolymer, Tocopherol, Hexyl Cinnamal, Silica, Isobutane, Benzyl Salicylate, Linalool, Alpha-Isomethyl Ionone, Benzyl Alcohol, Bht, Citronellol, May Contain: Titanium Dioxide, Iron Oxides, Ferric Ammonium Ferrocyanide.
how_to_use: Apply all over the face with your fingers or a brush, or use a beauty sponge to blend.

reviews.headline: Very nice coverage
reviews.comments: My skin does well with this foundation. Good coverage, excellent color match, lasts all day, does well over moisturizer

reviews.headline: I would buy this product again
reviews.comments: I love the coverage and the finish on this foundation. I love that it is affordable

reviews.headline: Great foundation!!!!
reviews.comments: This is a beautiful foundation. I am light/medium complexion and I do think that I could've went a shade or 2 darker. It has beautiful coverage and does last all day.

reviews.headline: Yes
reviews.comments: Always great customer service and very helpful employees.

reviews.headline: Terrible
reviews.comments: I bought this in two shades. Color match is terrible.  Wear is terrible.  Threw both bottles away.

reviews.headline: I would buy this again
reviews.comments: I love this foundation it's full coverage and I use it everyday

reviews.headline: Fungal acne safe product!
reviews.comments: I was a little skeptical to try this as I have very sensitive and acne/fungal acne prone skin but this so far has been amazing on my skin! It goes on and dries down matte and stays through out the day. I have oily skin and it doesn't breakdown the way my other urban decay foundation did. 9/10

reviews.headline: Would recommend
reviews.comments: Would recommend  this foundation has so much full coverage and it lasted all day

reviews.headline: Go to foundation
reviews.comments: I move around alot now that I switched roles at my job. This is the only foundation that I have that doesnt get oily and last all day. I get complimets all the time. I think I'll go a shade lighter because it does oxidize. Make sure to use a good primer, preferably with a matte finish.

reviews.headline: As good as the prestige ones
reviews.comments: I love this foundation, i use it for my every day makeup and love the extra spf protection. Love the finish and coverage. The only con is the shade range and the lack of undertones selection. I have an olive undertone amd i have to mix 2 different shades to make it work for my skin tone.

reviews.headline: Go to drugstore foundation
reviews.comments: This is a really great longwearing foundation. I find it very easy to apply evenly and it wears well throughout the day, especially when paired with a good primer and setting spray. It also sits well under other liquid or cream products.

reviews.headline: Just so bad
reviews.comments: It had so many issues. It dried down fast, was patchy, was cakey, and made me break out and my makeup never has made me breakout.

reviews.headline: HOLY GRAIL PLEASE NEVER DISCONTINUE
reviews.comments: Soooo beautiful look i look like kylie jenner i swear

reviews.headline: You don't need to break the bank for a flawless look
reviews.comments: Honestly, I'm extremely impressed by drugstore brands. They have stepped it up, and it's showing. The coverage is great, the texture is similar to Lancôme foundation very runny and light but packed with coverage and longevity. I think its a great foundation doesn't oxidize like I thought it would. The price is great for the quality you're receiving.

reviews.headline: This is now my forever foundation
reviews.comments: This is the first foundation that has given me coverage. The store associate Jackie was very knowledgeable and she was the one who recommended the product.

reviews.headline: Reformulation Is A NO GO
reviews.comments: Like others have said I have been using this foundation for years with no problems. I did not realize the formula changed until I received it in the mail with a red sticker that says "vitamin c". I am allergic to Vitamin C. I wish cosmetic companies would stop putting skincare in color cosmetics

reviews.headline: I had to return it
reviews.comments: No matter what shade I would buy it pulls so orange. The coverage is fantastic but I can't get the right shade match

reviews.headline: Holy Grail no more
reviews.comments: I wore the Loreal Infallible Freshwear 24 hour foundation for years. Summer 2024 i began the sesrch for a new foundation because the reformulation of Infallible includes Vitamin C, which my skin has a negative reaction to if the Vitamin C isn't 15% stabilized Vitamin C (THD Ascorbate).  It is rhe lesser common form of Vit C and typically not what cosmetic companies are using. Therefore, my face breaks out in tiny pustules.  It's been a long search for a foundation that offers the coversge, wear time and finish as the Infallible.  I've settled on Haus Labs Triclone foundation and Milani Conceal and Protect. Really wish makeup companies would stop adding Vitamin C! The amount is trace but enough to be bothersome if allergic.

reviews.headline: Devastating reformulation
reviews.comments: This was my holy grail foundation for years! Perfect coverage, perfect shade match, perfect price! Now since it's been reformulated, the shade is completely different. I'm very fair with pink undertones and the new formulation has caused my shade to lose the pink undertone to where it no longer works for me. I'm so sad and now on the hunt for a new foundation.

reviews.headline: Not full coverage
reviews.comments: The L'Oréal Infallible Foundation definitely falls short on the full coverage front. If you're looking to cover blemishes or uneven skin tone completely, this product won't be a great fit for you. As layering it doesn't always yield the desired effect, and you might still see some imperfections peeking through. Overall, it's not quite what I hoped for.

faceoff_positive.comments: I went on a mission to find my perfect foundation, or near as I could get, and this foundation ended that journey. I struggled to find a foundation that wouldn't grab onto my dry patches, gives medium/full coverage, and is truly fair and warm toned, and this foundation does it all! It gives my skin a healthy glow yet stays ALL day, as long as I don't touch my face. I bought True Beige, which has true a warm undertone (THANK YOU), and Porcelain which is more neutral. The only minor complaint I have is that it does sink into my smile lines a little, but I can deal with that–every foundation does that. This foundation is my ultimate favorite. It's nearly perfect, and I'm so, SO happy!
faceoff_positive.headline: AMAZING Foundation!

faceoff_negative.comments: This would honestly be my holy grail foundation if it wasn't for the fragrance. I don't understand why they would make such a great formula and then ruin it by including fragrance. So many people are sensitive to frangrance in products. People don't pick foundation based on how good it smells, so it's really unnecessary. It's also very high up on the ingredients list so there's a lot of it.
faceoff_negative.headline: Good but why so much fragrance?

rollup.name: Infallible Up to 32 Hour Fresh Wear Foundation
